The paper deals with the problem of drawing planar graphs on disk arrangements, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of clusters and pipes to route edges through the disks suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.DC).
